Name: Kenna
Text: Look, who’s new around here now?

Name: Player
Text: I’d say the same for you as I had just got higher placed.

Name: Kenna
Text: Better be careful, you can get kicked out of these races you know?

Name: Player
Text: I’m not afraid to be kicked out, you should.

Name: Kenna
Text: Whatever, while you’re at it- how about you quit and go back to your old grocery store job.

Name: Player
Text: A pleasure to be meeting you…

Name: Kenna
Text: A shame, you know the salon next door is hiring…

Name: Player
Text: Cool. I don’t care.

Name: Kenna
Text: Then you should, no one wants you here anyways.

Name: Player
Text: That’s nice

Name: Kenna
Text: Just go, alright? Find someone else to bother!

Name: Player
Text: Go find your mom, maybe she’ll comfort you.

Name: Kenna
Text: You’re so mean to me!

Name: None
Text: She walks off, angry and pouting for her own sanity. Good you aren’t like her.

Name: Adam
Text: Look what you did?

Name: Player
Text: What?

Name: None
Text: Adam walks off too, you know him from your old high school. He was always following after someone. You shouldn’t apologize to Kenna.

Name: None
Text: Charlie walks up, he’s done fixing your car and seems to be in a good mood.

Name: Charlie
Text: What was that all about?

Name: Player
Text: Nothing

Name: Charlie
Text: No, it is important. Tell me.

Name: Player
Text: Just Kenna and Adam.

Name: Charlie
Text: Well, those two are nothing to worry about. They have a sad life.

Name: Charlie
Text: Anyways, the next race is starting. Better beat them and their friends!
